label.value: neuron projection bundle connecting eye with brain

value.value: A neuron projection bundle that connects the retina or its analog in the eye with the brain. This includes the vertebrate optic nerve (not truly a nerve) as well as analogous structures such as the Bolwig nerve in Drosophila.

definition.value: for the vertebrate-specific structure, see UBERON:0000941 (cranial nerve II)

label.value: descending thin limb of loop of Henle

value.value: The descending thin limb is a part of the loop of Henle situated just after the proximal straight tubule (S3). It extends to the tip of the loop of Henle[GO].
The connecting tubule is a tubular segment of the nephron; it connects the distal convoluted tubule to the collecting duct[GO].

label.value: descending thin limb of loop of Henle 1

value.value: The short descending thin limb is the descending thin limb of a short nephron that has a squamous epithelial morphology[GO].
